subsection.def:
MPF
                    scheme
                    (強制性公積金計劃) means a registered scheme;

paragraph.content:
in the case of an ORSO exempted scheme or ORSO registered scheme which
                        is a group scheme under section 67 of the relevant Ordinance,
                        includes the representative employer of the scheme;

an amount not less than the past service liability of the existing member
                    has been or is to be transferred from the original scheme to the new scheme as a
                    result of the transfer;

subparagraph.content:
the eligibility requirements for members
                                                  of the original schemes to be transferred to the
                                                  new scheme;

paragraph.content:
if neither paragraph (a)(i)
            nor
            (ii) is applicable, the system which takes the place of a trust or such an insurance
            arrangement for the scheme;
            (E.R. 4 of
            2019)

the retirement, death or termination of the employment of a member of
                        the scheme or the occurrence of an event specified in the governing rules of
                        the scheme as an event which shall cause this section to apply;

subparagraph.content:
transferred from the existing scheme to a relevant scheme or registered
                        scheme and the relevant employer of the existing scheme is also the employer
                        of the scheme to which he is so transferred;

paragraph.content:
no trustee of the scheme shall pay out or otherwise dispose of any part of
                    the minimum MPF benefits to any new member of the scheme otherwise than in
                    accordance with the provisions of this Regulation;

no new member of the scheme shall have any right or entitlement to the
                    minimum MPF benefits otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this
                    Regulation;

evidence satisfactory to the trustee that the member has attained the
                        retirement age specified in Schedule 7 to the Ordinance;
                        and

subparagraph.content:
and age only is applicable, his age at the time of such
                                termination shall be used in determining his benefit
                                entitlements;

and age only is applicable, his age at the time of such
                                termination shall be used in determining his benefit
                                entitlements;

paragraph.content:
the number of employees who are not members of the scheme but who are
                    exempted (either in whole or in part) from the provisions of the Ordinance by
                    virtue of section 4 of the Ordinance;

subsection.def:
investment manager (投資經理), in relation to a scheme, means a person
                    appointed by a trustee of the scheme to manage the investment of the assets of
                    the scheme;

paragraph.content:
the duty to ensure that the assets of the scheme are invested in different
                    investments so as to minimize the risk of losses of those assets, unless in
                    particular circumstances it is prudent not to do so;

that he is a person of good reputation and character and, in
                        particular, has not been found guilty, whether in Hong Kong or elsewhere, of
                        an offence involving fraud or dishonesty;

subparagraph.content:
who, either alone or with others, is immediately responsible to the
                            directors of the company for the conduct of the whole of the business
                            carried on by the company in Hong Kong;
